This paper is about neural query graph ranking approaches for complex question answering over knowledge graphs. The task involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of knowledge graphs also suggests the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases), while the empirical investigation and proposed models indicate the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
